                    <td style='padding-right: 20px; vertical-align: top;'>
                      <img 
                        id='signature-logo-compact'
                        src='https://acquira.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/fav-light.png' 
                        alt='Company Logo' 
                        style='width: 60px; height: 60px; border-radius: 8px;'
                      />
                    </td>
                    <td style='vertical-align: top;'>
                      <div>
                        <div style='font-weight: bold; font-size: 16px; color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 4px;'>
                          <span id='signature-name-compact'>John Smith</span>
                        </div>
                        <div style='color: #525252; margin-bottom: 4px; font-size: 12px;'>
                          Cell: <span id='signature-phone-compact'>555-123-4567</span>
                        </div>
                        <div style='color: #525252; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 8px; font-size: 12px;'>
                          <span id='signature-role-compact'>Senior Consultant</span>
                        </div>
                        <div style='margin-bottom: 4px;'>
                          <a href='mailto:' id='signature-email-compact' style='color: #6366f1; text-decoration: none; font-size: 12px;'>john.smith@acquira.com</a>
                        </div>
                        <div style='margin-bottom: 8px;'>
                          <a href='#' id='signature-website-compact' style='color: #6366f1; text-decoration: none; font-size: 12px;'>www.acquira.com</a>
                        </div>
                        <div style='margin-bottom: 12px;'>
                          <a href='#' id='signature-calendly-compact' style='color: #6366f1; text-decoration: none; background: #f1f5f9; padding: 8px 16px; border-radius: 8px; display: inline-block; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; font-size: 12px;'>calendly.com/john-smith/30min</a>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                </table>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Instructions Section -->
        <div class='instructions'>
          <h3>How to Add This Signature to Gmail</h3>
          <ol class='list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm'>
            <li><strong>Copy:</strong> Click the "Copy Signature" button above</li>
            <li><strong>Settings:</strong> Open Gmail ‚Üí Click gear icon ‚Üí "See all settings"</li>
            <li><strong>General:</strong> Go to the "General" tab</li>
            <li><strong>Signature:</strong> Scroll to "Signature" section ‚Üí Click "Create new"</li>
            <li><strong>Name:</strong> Give your signature a name (e.g., "Professional")</li>
            <li><strong>Paste:</strong> Click in the signature editor and press <kbd>Ctrl+V</kbd> (or <kbd>Cmd+V</kbd> on Mac)</li>
            <li><strong>Verify:</strong> You should see the formatted signature (not HTML code)</li>
            <li><strong>Save:</strong> Scroll down ‚Üí Click "Save Changes"</li>
            <li><strong>Done:</strong> Your signature will appear in new emails automatically</li>
          </ol>
          <div style='margin-top: 16px; padding: 12px; background: #f0f9ff; border: 1px solid #bfdbfe; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 13px; color: #1e40af;'>
            <strong>Alternative Method:</strong> If copying doesn't work, manually select all the text in the preview above, copy it (Ctrl+C), then paste it directly into Gmail's signature editor.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

